First, make sure you have the latest version of the Spotify app installed on your phone. (You can find the latest version on Google Play or the App Store.)


Once you have the app installed and open, tap the three lines in the top left corner of the screen. From here, tap “Settings.”


Under “General,” tap “Subscription.”


Now, you’ll need to enter your payment information. If you have a premium account with Spotify, your billing address and payment method will be automatically filled in. If not, you’ll need to sign up for a premium account first before continuing.


After filling out your information, make sure “Auto Renew” is set to “Yes” and then tap “Save Changes.”


Now that your subscription is set up, all you need to do is keep an eye on your account settings page. Every month, Spotify will automatically renew your subscription unless you cancel it before then. (You canalways cancel your subscription at any time by going to the account settings page and tapping “Cancel Subscription.”)


